<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/8436> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #8436" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/7> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "p. 730, footnote 47" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7754> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7754" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cos. 191. An elogium, found at Luna, reads as follows: M: Acilius C. f. | Scarpea cepi (R. U. Inglieri, NSA 1952, fasc. 7-12, 20-ILLRP 321a). See MRR 1.352.[1]\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2207> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2207" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Being succeeded by Scipio, he returned to Rome to celebrate his triumph (Liv. 37.4.6-6.3, 7.7, and 46.2-6; cf. Polyb. 21.5.13; Caes. Bass. in GLK 6.265; see Degrassi 553). He gave gifts and privileges to Delphi (SIG\n     609-610; cf. 827 c- f; Roussel, BCH 56 [1932] 1-36; Daux, Delphes 227-233, and 255-260), and in Rome built an Aedes Pietatis (Liv. 40.34.5; Val. Max. 2.5.1). See also Grueber, CRRBM 1.169f.; Cesano, Stud. Num. 1.185f." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2169> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2169" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 35.24.5; 36.1.1; Fast. Cap., Degrassi 48f., 122, 454f.; Eutrop. 4.3; Chr. 354; Fast. Hyd.; Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod.; Zon. 9.19; and on Acilius, SIG\n     607. Acilius was assigned the war in Greece against Antiochus and the Aetolians, drove the former out of Greece by his victory at Thermopylae, then turned on the Aetolians, captured Heraclea, and after unsuccessful negotiations for peace besieged Naupactus\n     \n      1\n     \n     (Liv. 36.3.7-14, 14-21, and 22-35; 37.4.6-8; cf. Polyb. 20.9-10; Cic. Sen. 32; Val. Max. 2.5.1; Frontin. Str. 2.4.4; Plut. Cat. Mai. 13-14; Flam. 15-16; Philop. 17.4; Sull. 12.6; Flor. 1.24.10-11; App. Syr. 17-21; Iustin. 31.6.4-6; Eutrop. 4.3; Auct. Vir. Ill. 47.3; Oros. 4.20.20-21; see Legates and Trib. Mil. on Cato and L. Scipio). Nasica succeeded to the war with the Boii, whom he defeated, and after some dispute was permitted to celebrate a triumph (Liv. 36.1.8-9, and 2.1, and 38.5-7, and 39-40; 38.35.4; Act. Tr., Degrassi 78f., 553; Oros. 4.20.21). Acilius may have carried the Lex Acilia which placed intercalation under the power of the Pontifices (Macrob. Sat. 1.13.21)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2029> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2029" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Suppressed a slave conspiracy in Etruria (Liv. 33.36.2-3)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2028> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2028" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/3> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Election Liv. 33.24.2 Provinces and armies 33.26.1-4, and 43.7-8." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2017> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2017" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 33.25.2." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1956> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1956" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "M'. Acilius Glabrio succeeded M. Aurelius Cotta. Liv. 31.50.5." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1907> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1907" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Opposed Lentulus' desire for the province of Africa (Liv. 30.40.9-16), and carried a plebiscite confirming peace with Carthage (30.43.2-3; cf. Polyb. 15.18-19; Dio fr. 57.82-83; Zon. 9.14; see Promagistrates, on Scipio)." .
